name: GasyCar
product_desc:
GasyCar is a car sharing app designed to meet the specificities of Madagascar. It mostly uses the same principles as classic car sharing save for the fact that Malagasy people scarcely have credit cards, so, the payment for GasyCar will be on-the-spot using a yearly subscription system. Hitchhiking is common currency here  but not formalized. Otherwise, people without a car get about using vehicles called taxi-brousse and looking like small buses which are quite uncomfortable.
GasyCar is aimed at offering an alternate means of tansportation to Malagasy people.
PS: The product is built already, but the team is still under construction.
high_concept: The very first car sharing app for Madagascar

name: Onja
product_desc: In a nutshell we handpick highly intelligent teenagers from extremely poor communities. We groom them into brilliant coders, then employ them to make software. They earn a life changing salary, and we, the organisation makes a profit, which we use to educate more students, and the cycle continues. We’re starting in Madagascar, home to some of the world’s poorest, and most deserving people.

name: ARIARY.NET
product_desc:
Ariary.net is a platform for online payment in Malagasy currency Ariary.
Ariary.net lets malagasy people create their own ecommerce and ebusiness. 
The “Ariary.net” project is an innovation in the financial landscape in Madagascar. There is NO online payment service in Madagascar before 2014.
Ariary.net is creating a centralized service of online payment with mobile money and international credit card. Mobile money payment is secure, immediate and very useful. This will be a PayPal for Malagasy People.
Our ambition is to widely disseminate these new payment systems in order to provide better and secure services to businesses. Our target is the entire population, bankable or not.
high_concept: Online payment service provider in Madagascar
markets: Financial Services, E-Commerce, B2B, Mobile Payments
